HEADWORD: Trisacramentarian
<hw>Tri*sac`ra*men*ta"ri*an</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>tri-</ets> + <ets>sacramentarian</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Eccl.)</fld>
<def>One who recognizes three sacraments, and no more; -- namely,
baptism, the Lord's Supper, and penance. See
<er>Sacrament</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

